Message:
Hi there similar situation as u

SG Citizen born and bred in sg holding sg passport  msia myPR red card holder

Officially the answer still appears to be no

Each time I go in I ask the kastam officer I get a diff responsereason but most of the answers revolve arnd no

Reason is because myPR holders use a different method of 2FA to authenticate entry and exit ie SG Biometric Passport  myPR chip

Only manual counters have the machine to read from chip directly Same as if Malaysian citizen presents their myKad

There are too few myPR holders using land checkpoints to justify installation of the device at all the e gates Hence they never implement

My friend who is also a myPR holder kennacan enter egate on entry via woodlands but on exit fail Go manual counter to clear got warned of potential offence for failing to register myPR card info on entry I am also smlj

Those with a similar immigration profile and can clear e gate do at ur own risk Just sharing
